The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 UTI Growth amp; Value Fund (annual dividend plan) has declared a 25 per cent dividend and March 10 has been fixed as the record date. UTI Basic Industries Fund has also declared a 12 per cent dividend with the same record date. As on February 24, the NAVs of growth amp; value and basic industries fund stood at Rs 19.62 and Rs 13.25, respectively.

 Chola Mutual Fund has revised the load structure for its multi-cap fund. The entry load would be 2.25 per cent for an investment up to Rs 1 crore. However, there will be no entry load for investments above Rs 1 crore and those made under Systematic Investment Plan (SIP) and Systematic Transfer Plan (STP). An exit load of 2.25 per cent would be levied if investments made under SIP and STP are redeemed within one year of allotment.

 HDFC Mutual Fund has announced March 18 as the record date for dividend distribution under HDFC Prudence and HDFC Balanced fund. The NAV was Rs 24.885 and Rs 18.535, respectively, as on February 24. 

 Reliance Mutual Fund has introduced dividend pay-out and monthly dividend re-investment options under the retail plan and institutional plan of Reliance Liquid Fund (Treasury Plan).




